Text: Hi, this My90! We’re here to collect feedback about your experience with Gotham PD. We are independent, and everything you send will be anonymous. Standard msg & data rates apply. Reply HELP for help or STOP to unsubscribe. Ready to begin? Text “OK” to get started.
How much do you agree with the following statement: During the encounter, the officer treated me with dignity and respect.
How much do you agree with the following statement: During the encounter, the officer discriminated against me because of my race, gender, age, religion, or sexual orientation.
How much do you agree with the following statement: During the encounter, the officer clearly explained the reasons for his or her actions.
How well are the police who work in your neighborhood doing at dealing with problems that concern our neighborhood?
How well are the police who work in your neighborhood doing at treating people fairly regardless of who they are?
How much do you agree with the following statement: I trust my police department to make decisions that are good for everyone in my city.
How much do you agree with the following statement: I have confidence that my police department can do its job well.
How likely would you be to work with the police to identify a person who has committed a crime in your neighborhood?
How likely would you be to attend a meeting of residents in your neighborhood to discuss crime prevention?
How safe do you feel, or would you feel, being alone outside in your neighborhood at night?
Anything else you would like to add about your experience with the Gotham PD? Text your thoughts now or “skip” to continue.
Now a few questions about you. Have you ever previously interacted with the Gotham PD?
Which gender do you identify with?
Which ethnic group do you identify with most?
What is your zip code? Please text the number.
Thank you very much for sharing your valuable feedback. If there is anything else you would like to add, please text it now. You can find more information online at www.textmy90.com/irving.
